  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Beijing, June 20 (XINHUA) -- Floods continue to have serious effects in Guangdong, Hunan and Jiangxi Provinces and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in southern China.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The flood peak on the Beijiang River in Guangdong Province passed through Qingyuan city by 23:00 hours last night, and the water level was recorded as 14.72 m, about 4.22 m above the danger mark; the speed was 17,400 cu m per second.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters has sent special teams of people to help fight floods in Hunan and Jiangxi.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   In the drought-stricken areas, 12 million people and 12 million head of livestock are short of drinking water, according to the State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters.
  </a>
